Reasoning: The paper discusses the synthesis of Computational Complexity Theory with Recursive Analysis to provide a quantitative foundation for reliable numerics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the operators of maximization, integration, and solving ordinary differential equations, which are commonly used in numerical analysis, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of Gevrey's hierarchy of functions and the Theory of Computation suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). Finally, the use of Hard Analysis and Information-Based Complexity suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
